init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A world-wide society of mutants has emerged and are now the way of life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A world without the Internet was a hard one for me to adjust to.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I was nervous as I prepared for the interview, but I had done my homework and knew as much about this new reality as possible.
